93QLocale::Language QLocalePrivate::codeToLanguage(QStringView code,
94 QLocale::LanguageCodeTypes codeTypes) noexcept
95{
96 const auto len = code.size();
97 if (len != 2 && len != 3)
98 return QLocale::AnyLanguage;
99
100 const char16_t uc1 = code[0].toLower().unicode();
101 const char16_t uc2 = code[1].toLower().unicode();
102 const char16_t uc3 = len > 2 ? code[2].toLower().unicode() : 0;
103
104 // All language codes are ASCII.
105 if (uc1 > 0x7F || uc2 > 0x7F || uc3 > 0x7F)
106 return QLocale::AnyLanguage;
107
108 const AlphaCode codeBuf = { .code: { char(uc1), char(uc2), char(uc3) } };
109
110 auto searchCode = [codeBuf](auto f) {
111 return std::find_if(languageCodeList.begin(), languageCodeList.end(),
112 [=](const LanguageCodeEntry &i) { return f(i) == codeBuf; });
113 };
114
115 if (codeTypes.testFlag(flag: QLocale::ISO639Part1) && uc3 == 0) {
116 auto i = searchCode([](const LanguageCodeEntry &i) { return i.part1; });
117 if (i != languageCodeList.end())
118 return QLocale::Language(std::distance(first: languageCodeList.begin(), last: i));
119 }
120
121 if (uc3 != 0) {
122 if (codeTypes.testFlag(flag: QLocale::ISO639Part2B)) {
123 auto i = searchCode([](const LanguageCodeEntry &i) { return i.part2B; });
124 if (i != languageCodeList.end())
125 return QLocale::Language(std::distance(first: languageCodeList.begin(), last: i));
126 }
127
128 // Optimization: Part 2T code if present is always the same as Part 3 code.
129 // This is asserted in iso639_3.LanguageCodeData.
130 if (codeTypes.testFlag(flag: QLocale::ISO639Part2T)
131 && !codeTypes.testFlag(flag: QLocale::ISO639Part3)) {
132 auto i = searchCode([](const LanguageCodeEntry &i) { return i.part2T; });
133 if (i != languageCodeList.end())
134 return QLocale::Language(std::distance(first: languageCodeList.begin(), last: i));
135 }
136
137 if (codeTypes.testFlag(flag: QLocale::ISO639Part3)) {
138 auto i = searchCode([](const LanguageCodeEntry &i) { return i.part3; });
139 if (i != languageCodeList.end())
140 return QLocale::Language(std::distance(first: languageCodeList.begin(), last: i));
141 }
142 }
143
144 if (codeTypes.testFlag(flag: QLocale::LegacyLanguageCode) && uc3 == 0) {
145 // legacy codes
146 if (uc1 == 'n' && uc2 == 'o') // no -> nb
147 return QLocale::NorwegianBokmal;
148 if (uc1 == 't' && uc2 == 'l') // tl -> fil
149 return QLocale::Filipino;
150 if (uc1 == 's' && uc2 == 'h') // sh -> sr[_Latn]
151 return QLocale::Serbian;
152 if (uc1 == 'm' && uc2 == 'o') // mo -> ro
153 return QLocale::Romanian;
154 // Android uses the following deprecated codes
155 if (uc1 == 'i' && uc2 == 'w') // iw -> he
156 return QLocale::Hebrew;
157 if (uc1 == 'i' && uc2 == 'n') // in -> id
158 return QLocale::Indonesian;
159 if (uc1 == 'j' && uc2 == 'i') // ji -> yi
160 return QLocale::Yiddish;
161 }
162 return QLocale::AnyLanguage;
163}

165QLocale::Script QLocalePrivate::codeToScript(QStringView code) noexcept
166{
167 const auto len = code.size();
168 if (len != 4)
169 return QLocale::AnyScript;
170
171 // script is titlecased in our data
172 unsigned char c0 = code[0].toUpper().toLatin1();
173 unsigned char c1 = code[1].toLower().toLatin1();
174 unsigned char c2 = code[2].toLower().toLatin1();
175 unsigned char c3 = code[3].toLower().toLatin1();
176
177 const unsigned char *c = script_code_list;
178 for (qsizetype i = 0; i < QLocale::LastScript; ++i, c += 4) {
179 if (c0 == c[0] && c1 == c[1] && c2 == c[2] && c3 == c[3])
180 return QLocale::Script(i);
181 }
182 return QLocale::AnyScript;
183}
184
185QLocale::Territory QLocalePrivate::codeToTerritory(QStringView code) noexcept
186{
187 const auto len = code.size();
188 if (len != 2 && len != 3)
189 return QLocale::AnyTerritory;
190
191 char16_t uc1 = code[0].toUpper().unicode();
192 char16_t uc2 = code[1].toUpper().unicode();
193 char16_t uc3 = len > 2 ? code[2].toUpper().unicode() : 0;
194
195 const unsigned char *c = territory_code_list;
196 for (; *c != 0; c += 3) {
197 if (uc1 == c[0] && uc2 == c[1] && uc3 == c[2])
198 return QLocale::Territory((c - territory_code_list)/3);
199 }
200
201 return QLocale::AnyTerritory;
202}

204QLatin1StringView QLocalePrivate::languageToCode(QLocale::Language language,
205 QLocale::LanguageCodeTypes codeTypes)
206{
207 if (language == QLocale::AnyLanguage || language > QLocale::LastLanguage)
208 return {};
209 if (language == QLocale::C)
210 return "C"_L1;
211
212 const LanguageCodeEntry &i = languageCodeList[language];
213
214 if (codeTypes.testFlag(flag: QLocale::ISO639Part1) && i.part1.isValid())
215 return {i.part1.code, 2};
216
217 if (codeTypes.testFlag(flag: QLocale::ISO639Part2B) && i.part2B.isValid())
218 return {i.part2B.code, 3};
219
220 if (codeTypes.testFlag(flag: QLocale::ISO639Part2T) && i.part2T.isValid())
221 return {i.part2T.code, 3};
222
223 if (codeTypes.testFlag(flag: QLocale::ISO639Part3))
224 return {i.part3.code, 3};
225
226 return {};
227}
228
229QLatin1StringView QLocalePrivate::scriptToCode(QLocale::Script script)
230{
231 if (script == QLocale::AnyScript || script > QLocale::LastScript)
232 return {};
233 const unsigned char *c = script_code_list + 4 * script;
234 return {reinterpret_cast<const char *>(c), 4};
235}
236
237QLatin1StringView QLocalePrivate::territoryToCode(QLocale::Territory territory)
238{
239 if (territory == QLocale::AnyTerritory || territory > QLocale::LastTerritory)
240 return {};
241
242 const unsigned char *c = territory_code_list + 3 * territory;
243 return {reinterpret_cast<const char*>(c), c[2] == 0 ? 2 : 3};
244}

246namespace {
247struct LikelyPair
248{
249 QLocaleId key; // Search key.
250 QLocaleId value = QLocaleId { .language_id: 0, .script_id: 0, .territory_id: 0 };
251};
252
253bool operator<(const LikelyPair &lhs, const LikelyPair &rhs)
254{
255 // Must match the comparison LocaleDataWriter.likelySubtags() uses when
256 // sorting, see qtbase/util/locale_database.qlocalexml2cpp.py
257 const auto compare = [](int lhs, int rhs) {
258 // 0 sorts after all other values; lhs and rhs are passed ushort values.
259 const int huge = 0x10000;
260 return (lhs ? lhs : huge) - (rhs ? rhs : huge);
261 };
262 const auto &left = lhs.key;
263 const auto &right = rhs.key;
264 // Comparison order: language, region, script:
265 if (int cmp = compare(left.language_id, right.language_id))
266 return cmp < 0;
267 if (int cmp = compare(left.territory_id, right.territory_id))
268 return cmp < 0;
269 return compare(left.script_id, right.script_id) < 0;
270}
271} // anonymous namespace
272
273/*!
274 Fill in blank fields of a locale ID.
275
276 An ID in which some fields are zero stands for any locale that agrees with
277 it in its non-zero fields. CLDR's likely-subtag data is meant to help us
278 chose which candidate to prefer. (Note, however, that CLDR does have some
279 cases where it maps an ID to a "best match" for which CLDR does not provide
280 data, even though there are locales for which CLDR does provide data that do
281 match the given ID. It's telling us, unhelpfully but truthfully, what
282 locale would (most likely) be meant by (someone using) the combination
283 requested, even when that locale isn't yet supported.) It may also map an
284 obsolete or generic tag to a modern or more specific replacement, possibly
285 filling in some of the other fields in the process (presently only for
286 countries). Note that some fields of the result may remain blank, but there
287 is no more specific recommendation available.
288
289 For the formal specification, see
290 https://www.unicode.org/reports/tr35/#Likely_Subtags
291
292 \note We also search und_script_region and und_region; they're not mentioned
293 in the spec, but the examples clearly presume them and CLDR does provide
294 such likely matches.
295*/
296QLocaleId QLocaleId::withLikelySubtagsAdded() const
297{
298 /* Each pattern that appears in a comments below, language_script_region and
299 similar, indicates which of this's fields (even if blank) are being
300 attended to in a given search; for fields left out of the pattern, the
301 search uses 0 regardless of whether this has specified the field.
302
303 If a key matches what we're searching for (possibly with a wildcard in
304 the key matching a non-wildcard in our search), the tags from this that
305 are specified in the key are replaced by the match (even if different);
306 but the other tags of this replace what's in the match (even when the
307 match does specify a value).
308 */
309 static_assert(std::size(likely_subtags) % 2 == 0);
310 auto *pairs = reinterpret_cast<const LikelyPair *>(likely_subtags);
311 auto *const afterPairs = pairs + std::size(likely_subtags) / 2;
312 LikelyPair sought { .key: *this };
313 // Our array is sorted in the order that puts all candidate matches in the
314 // order we would want them; ones we should prefer appear before the others.
315 if (language_id) {
316 // language_script_region, language_region, language_script, language:
317 pairs = std::lower_bound(pairs, afterPairs, sought);
318 // Single language's block isn't long enough to warrant more binary
319 // chopping within it - just traverse it all:
320 for (; pairs < afterPairs && pairs->key.language_id == language_id; ++pairs) {
321 const QLocaleId &key = pairs->key;
322 if (key.territory_id && key.territory_id != territory_id)
323 continue;
324 if (key.script_id && key.script_id != script_id)
325 continue;
326 QLocaleId value = pairs->value;
327 if (territory_id && !key.territory_id)
328 value.territory_id = territory_id;
329 if (script_id && !key.script_id)
330 value.script_id = script_id;
331 return value;
332 }
333 }
334 // und_script_region or und_region (in that order):
335 if (territory_id) {
336 sought.key = QLocaleId { .language_id: 0, .script_id: script_id, .territory_id: territory_id };
337 pairs = std::lower_bound(pairs, afterPairs, sought);
338 // Again, individual und_?_region block isn't long enough to make binary
339 // chop a win:
340 for (; pairs < afterPairs && pairs->key.territory_id == territory_id; ++pairs) {
341 const QLocaleId &key = pairs->key;
342 Q_ASSERT(!key.language_id);
343 if (key.script_id && key.script_id != script_id)
344 continue;
345 QLocaleId value = pairs->value;
346 if (language_id)
347 value.language_id = language_id;
348 if (script_id && !key.script_id)
349 value.script_id = script_id;
350 return value;
351 }
352 }
353 // und_script:
354 if (script_id) {
355 sought.key = QLocaleId { .language_id: 0, .script_id: script_id, .territory_id: 0 };
356 pairs = std::lower_bound(pairs, afterPairs, sought);
357 if (pairs < afterPairs && pairs->key.script_id == script_id) {
358 Q_ASSERT(!pairs->key.language_id && !pairs->key.territory_id);
359 QLocaleId value = pairs->value;
360 if (language_id)
361 value.language_id = language_id;
362 if (territory_id)
363 value.territory_id = territory_id;
364 return value;
365 }
366 }
367 if (matchesAll()) { // Skipped all of the above.
368 // CLDR has no match-all at v37, but might get one some day ...
369 pairs = std::lower_bound(pairs, afterPairs, sought);
370 if (pairs < afterPairs) {
371 // All other keys are < match-all.
372 Q_ASSERT(pairs + 1 == afterPairs);
373 Q_ASSERT(pairs->key.matchesAll());
374 return pairs->value;
375 }
376 }
377 return *this;
378}
379
380QLocaleId QLocaleId::withLikelySubtagsRemoved() const
381{
382 QLocaleId max = withLikelySubtagsAdded();
383 // language
384 {
385 QLocaleId id { .language_id: language_id, .script_id: 0, .territory_id: 0 };
386 if (id.withLikelySubtagsAdded() == max)
387 return id;
388 }
389 // language_region
390 if (territory_id) {
391 QLocaleId id { .language_id: language_id, .script_id: 0, .territory_id: territory_id };
392 if (id.withLikelySubtagsAdded() == max)
393 return id;
394 }
395 // language_script
396 if (script_id) {
397 QLocaleId id { .language_id: language_id, .script_id: script_id, .territory_id: 0 };
398 if (id.withLikelySubtagsAdded() == max)
399 return id;
400 }
401 return max;
402}

404QByteArray QLocaleId::name(char separator) const
405{
406 if (language_id == QLocale::AnyLanguage)
407 return QByteArray();
408 if (language_id == QLocale::C)
409 return QByteArrayLiteral("C");
410
411 const LanguageCodeEntry &language = languageCodeList[language_id];
412 const char *lang;
413 qsizetype langLen;
414
415 if (language.part1.isValid()) {
416 lang = language.part1.code;
417 langLen = 2;
418 } else {
419 lang = language.part2B.isValid() ? language.part2B.code : language.part3.code;
420 langLen = 3;
421 }
422
423 const unsigned char *script =
424 (script_id != QLocale::AnyScript ? script_code_list + 4 * script_id : nullptr);
425 const unsigned char *country =
426 (territory_id != QLocale::AnyTerritory
427 ? territory_code_list + 3 * territory_id : nullptr);
428 qsizetype len = langLen + (script ? 4 + 1 : 0) + (country ? (country[2] != 0 ? 3 : 2) + 1 : 0);
429 QByteArray name(len, Qt::Uninitialized);
430 char *uc = name.data();
431
432 *uc++ = lang[0];
433 *uc++ = lang[1];
434 if (langLen > 2)
435 *uc++ = lang[2];
436
437 if (script) {
438 *uc++ = separator;
439 *uc++ = script[0];
440 *uc++ = script[1];
441 *uc++ = script[2];
442 *uc++ = script[3];
443 }
444 if (country) {
445 *uc++ = separator;
446 *uc++ = country[0];
447 *uc++ = country[1];
448 if (country[2] != 0)
449 *uc++ = country[2];
450 }
451 return name;
452}

454QByteArray QLocalePrivate::bcp47Name(char separator) const
455{
456 if (m_data->m_language_id == QLocale::AnyLanguage)
457 return QByteArray();
458 if (m_data->m_language_id == QLocale::C)
459 return QByteArrayLiteral("en");
460
461 return m_data->id().withLikelySubtagsRemoved().name(separator);
462}

464static qsizetype findLocaleIndexById(const QLocaleId &localeId)
465{
466 qsizetype idx = locale_index[localeId.language_id];
467 // If there are no locales for specified language (so we we've got the
468 // default language, which has no associated script or country), give up:
469 if (localeId.language_id && idx == 0)
470 return idx;
471
472 Q_ASSERT(localeId.acceptLanguage(locale_data[idx].m_language_id));
473
474 do {
475 if (localeId.acceptScriptTerritory(other: locale_data[idx].id()))
476 return idx;
477 ++idx;
478 } while (localeId.acceptLanguage(lang: locale_data[idx].m_language_id));
479
480 return -1;
481}
482
483qsizetype QLocaleData::findLocaleIndex(QLocaleId lid)
484{
485 QLocaleId localeId = lid;
486 QLocaleId likelyId = localeId.withLikelySubtagsAdded();
487 const ushort fallback = likelyId.language_id;
488
489 // Try a straight match with the likely data:
490 qsizetype index = findLocaleIndexById(localeId: likelyId);
491 if (index >= 0)
492 return index;
493 QVarLengthArray<QLocaleId, 6> tried;
494 tried.push_back(t: likelyId);
495
496#define CheckCandidate(id) do { \
497 if (!tried.contains(id)) { \
498 index = findLocaleIndexById(id); \
499 if (index >= 0) \
500 return index; \
501 tried.push_back(id); \
502 } \
503 } while (false) // end CheckCandidate
504
505 // No match; try again with raw data:
506 CheckCandidate(localeId);
507
508 // No match; try again with likely country for language_script
509 if (lid.territory_id && (lid.language_id || lid.script_id)) {
510 localeId.territory_id = 0;
511 likelyId = localeId.withLikelySubtagsAdded();
512 CheckCandidate(likelyId);
513
514 // No match; try again with any country
515 CheckCandidate(localeId);
516 }
517
518 // No match; try again with likely script for language_region
519 if (lid.script_id && (lid.language_id || lid.territory_id)) {
520 localeId = QLocaleId { .language_id: lid.language_id, .script_id: 0, .territory_id: lid.territory_id };
521 likelyId = localeId.withLikelySubtagsAdded();
522 CheckCandidate(likelyId);
523
524 // No match; try again with any script
525 CheckCandidate(localeId);
526 }
527#undef CheckCandidate
528
529 // No match; return base index for initial likely language:
530 return locale_index[fallback];
531}

533static QStringView findTag(QStringView name) noexcept
534{
535 const std::u16string_view v(name.utf16(), size_t(name.size()));
536 const auto i = v.find_first_of(str: u"_-.@");
537 if (i == std::string_view::npos)
538 return name;
539 return name.first(n: qsizetype(i));
540}
541
542static bool validTag(QStringView tag)
543{
544 // Is tag is a non-empty sequence of ASCII letters and/or digits ?
545 for (QChar uc : tag) {
546 const char16_t ch = uc.unicode();
547 if (!isAsciiLetterOrNumber(c: ch))
548 return false;
549 }
550 return tag.size() > 0;
551}
552
553static bool isScript(QStringView tag)
554{
555 // Every script name is 4 characters, a capital followed by three lower-case;
556 // so a search for tag in allScripts *can* only match if it's aligned.
557 static const QString allScripts =
558 QString::fromLatin1(str: reinterpret_cast<const char *>(script_code_list),
559 size: sizeof(script_code_list) - 1);
560 return tag.size() == 4 && allScripts.indexOf(s: tag) % 4 == 0;
561}
562
563bool qt_splitLocaleName(QStringView name, QStringView *lang, QStringView *script, QStringView *land)
564{
565 // Assume each of lang, script and land is nullptr or points to an empty QStringView.
566 enum ParserState { NoState, LangState, ScriptState, CountryState };
567 ParserState state = LangState;
568 while (name.size() && state != NoState) {
569 const QStringView tag = findTag(name);
570 if (!validTag(tag))
571 break;
572 name = name.sliced(pos: tag.size());
573 const bool sep = name.size() > 0;
574 if (sep) // tag wasn't all that remained; there was a separator
575 name = name.sliced(pos: 1);
576
577 switch (state) {
578 case LangState:
579 if (tag.size() != 2 && tag.size() != 3)
580 return false;
581 if (lang)
582 *lang = tag;
583 state = sep ? ScriptState : NoState;
584 break;
585 case ScriptState:
586 if (isScript(tag)) {
587 if (script)
588 *script = tag;
589 state = sep ? CountryState : NoState;
590 break;
591 }
592 // It wasn't a script, assume it's a country.
593 Q_FALLTHROUGH();
594 case CountryState:
595 if (land)
596 *land = tag;
597 state = NoState;
598 break;
599 case NoState: // Precluded by loop condition !
600 Q_UNREACHABLE();
601 break;
602 }
603 }
604 return state != LangState;
605}
606
607QLocaleId QLocaleId::fromName(QStringView name)
608{
609 QStringView lang;
610 QStringView script;
611 QStringView land;
612 if (!qt_splitLocaleName(name, lang: &lang, script: &script, land: &land))
613 return { .language_id: QLocale::C, .script_id: 0, .territory_id: 0 };
614
615 QLocale::Language langId = QLocalePrivate::codeToLanguage(code: lang);
616 if (langId == QLocale::AnyLanguage)
617 return { .language_id: QLocale::C, .script_id: 0, .territory_id: 0 };
618 return { .language_id: langId, .script_id: QLocalePrivate::codeToScript(code: script), .territory_id: QLocalePrivate::codeToTerritory(code: land) };
619}

621QString qt_readEscapedFormatString(QStringView format, qsizetype *idx)
622{
623 qsizetype &i = *idx;
624
625 Q_ASSERT(format.at(i) == u'\'');
626 ++i;
627 if (i == format.size())
628 return QString();
629 if (format.at(n: i).unicode() == '\'') { // "''" outside of a quoted string
630 ++i;
631 return "'"_L1;
632 }
633
634 QString result;
635
636 while (i < format.size()) {
637 if (format.at(n: i).unicode() == '\'') {
638 if (format.mid(pos: i + 1).startsWith(c: u'\'')) {
639 // "''" inside a quoted string
640 result.append(c: u'\'');
641 i += 2;
642 } else {
643 break;
644 }
645 } else {
646 result.append(c: format.at(n: i++));
647 }
648 }
649 if (i < format.size())
650 ++i;
651
652 return result;
653}
654
655/*!
656 \internal
657
658 Counts the number of identical leading characters in \a s.
659
660 If \a s is empty, returns 0.
661
662 Otherwise, returns the number of consecutive \c{s.front()}
663 characters at the start of \a s.
664
665 \code
666 qt_repeatCount(u"a"); // == 1
667 qt_repeatCount(u"ab"); // == 1
668 qt_repeatCount(u"aab"); // == 2
669 \endcode
670*/
671qsizetype qt_repeatCount(QStringView s)
672{
673 if (s.isEmpty())
674 return 0;
675 const QChar c = s.front();
676 qsizetype j = 1;
677 while (j < s.size() && s.at(n: j) == c)
678 ++j;
679 return j;
680}

691/******************************************************************************
692** Default system locale behavior

694
695/*!
696 \internal
697 Constructs a QSystemLocale object.
698
699 The constructor will automatically install this object as the system locale.
700 It and the destructor maintain a stack of system locales, with the
701 most-recently-created instance (that hasn't yet been deleted) used as the
702 system locale. This is only intended as a way to let a platform plugin
703 install its own system locale, overriding what might otherwise be provided
704 for its class of platform (as Android does, differing from Linux), and to
705 let tests transiently over-ride the system or plugin-supplied one. As such,
706 there should not be diverse threads creating and destroying QSystemLocale
707 instances concurrently, so no attempt is made at thread-safety in managing
708 the stack.
709
710 This constructor also resets the flag that'll prompt QLocale::system() to
711 re-initialize its data, so that instantiating a QSystemLocale (even
712 transiently) triggers a refresh of the system locale's data. This is
713 exploited by some test code.
714*/
715QSystemLocale::QSystemLocale() : next(_systemLocale)
716{
717 _systemLocale = this;
718
719 systemLocaleData.m_language_id = 0;
720}
721
722/*!
723 \internal
724 Deletes the object.
725*/
726QSystemLocale::~QSystemLocale()
727{
728 if (_systemLocale == this) {
729 _systemLocale = next;
730
731 // Change to system locale => force refresh.
732 systemLocaleData.m_language_id = 0;
733 } else {
734 for (QSystemLocale *p = _systemLocale; p; p = p->next) {
735 if (p->next == this)
736 p->next = next;
737 }
738 }
739}
740
741static const QSystemLocale *systemLocale()
742{
743 if (_systemLocale)
744 return _systemLocale;
745
746 // As this is only ever instantiated with _systemLocale null, it is
747 // necessarily the ->next-most in any chain that may subsequently develop;
748 // and it won't be destructed until exit()-time.
749 static QSystemLocale globalInstance;
750 return &globalInstance;
751}
752
753static void updateSystemPrivate()
754{
755 // This function is NOT thread-safe!
756 // It *should not* be called by anything but systemData()
757 // It *is* called before {system,default}LocalePrivate exist.
758 const QSystemLocale *sys_locale = systemLocale();
759
760 // tell the object that the system locale has changed.
761 sys_locale->query(QSystemLocale::LocaleChanged);
762
763 // Populate system locale with fallback as basis
764 systemLocaleData = locale_data[sys_locale->fallbackLocaleIndex()];
765
766 QVariant res = sys_locale->query(QSystemLocale::LanguageId);
767 if (!res.isNull()) {
768 systemLocaleData.m_language_id = res.toInt();
769 systemLocaleData.m_script_id = QLocale::AnyScript; // default for compatibility
770 }
771 res = sys_locale->query(QSystemLocale::TerritoryId);
772 if (!res.isNull()) {
773 systemLocaleData.m_territory_id = res.toInt();
774 systemLocaleData.m_script_id = QLocale::AnyScript; // default for compatibility
775 }
776 res = sys_locale->query(QSystemLocale::ScriptId);
777 if (!res.isNull())
778 systemLocaleData.m_script_id = res.toInt();
779
780 // Should we replace Any values based on likely sub-tags ?
781}
782#endif // !QT_NO_SYSTEMLOCALE
783
784static const QLocaleData *systemData()
785{
786#ifndef QT_NO_SYSTEMLOCALE
787 /*
788 Copy over the information from the fallback locale and modify.
789
790 This modifies (cross-thread) global state, so take care to only call it in
791 one thread.
792 */
793 {
794 Q_CONSTINIT static QBasicMutex systemDataMutex;
795 systemDataMutex.lock();
796 if (systemLocaleData.m_language_id == 0)
797 updateSystemPrivate();
798 systemDataMutex.unlock();
799 }
800
801 return &systemLocaleData;
802#else
803 return locale_data;
804#endif
805}

858static QLocalePrivate *localePrivateByName(QStringView name)
859{
860 if (name == u"C")
861 return c_private();

863 Q_ASSERT(index >= 0 && index < locale_data_size);

865 locale_data[index].m_language_id == QLocale::C
866 ? QLocale::OmitGroupSeparator : QLocale::DefaultNumberOptions);

868
869static QLocalePrivate *findLocalePrivate(QLocale::Language language, QLocale::Script script,
870 QLocale::Territory territory)
871{
872 if (language == QLocale::C)
873 return c_private();
874
875 qsizetype index = QLocaleData::findLocaleIndex(lid: QLocaleId { .language_id: language, .script_id: script, .territory_id: territory });
876 Q_ASSERT(index >= 0 && index < locale_data_size);
877 const QLocaleData *data = locale_data + index;
878
879 QLocale::NumberOptions numberOptions = QLocale::DefaultNumberOptions;
880
881 // If not found, should use default locale:
882 if (data->m_language_id == QLocale::C) {
883 if (defaultLocalePrivate.exists())
884 numberOptions = defaultLocalePrivate->data()->m_numberOptions;
885 data = defaultData();
886 index = defaultIndex();
887 }
888 return new QLocalePrivate(data, index, numberOptions);
889}

893{
894#ifndef QT_NO_SYSTEMLOCALE

896 return std::nullopt;

900 return std::nullopt;

903#else

905 Q_UNUSED(type)
906 return std::nullopt;

982/*!
983 \since 6.3
984
985 Constructs a QLocale object with the specified \a name.
986
987 The name has the format "language[_script][_territory][.codeset][@modifier]"
988 or "C", where:
989
990 \list
991 \li language is a lowercase, two-letter, ISO 639 language code (some
992 three-letter codes are also recognized),
993 \li script is a capitalized, four-letter, ISO 15924 script code,
994 \li territory is an uppercase, two-letter, ISO 3166 territory code
995 (some numeric codes are also recognized), and
996 \li codeset and modifier are ignored.
997 \endlist
998
999 The separator can be either underscore \c{'_'} (U+005F, "low line") or a
1000 dash \c{'-'} (U+002D, "hyphen-minus"). If QLocale has no data for the
1001 specified combination of language, script, and territory, then it uses the
1002 most suitable match it can find instead. If the string violates the locale
1003 format, or no suitable data can be found for the specified keys, the "C"
1004 locale is used instead.
1005
1006 This constructor is much slower than QLocale(Language, Script, Territory) or
1007 QLocale(Language, Territory).
1008
1009 \sa bcp47Name(), {Matching combinations of language, script and territory}
1010*/
1011QLocale::QLocale(QStringView name)
1012 : d(localePrivateByName(name))
1013{
1014}

1158/*!
1159 \fn QString QLocale::quoteString(const QString &str, QuotationStyle style) const
1160
1161 \since 4.8
1162
1163 Returns \a str quoted according to the current locale using the given
1164 quotation \a style.
1165*/
1166
1167/*!
1168 \since 6.0
1169
1170 \overload
1171*/
1172QString QLocale::quoteString(QStringView str, QuotationStyle style) const
1173{
1174#ifndef QT_NO_SYSTEMLOCALE
1175 if (d->m_data == &systemLocaleData) {
1176 QVariant res;
1177 if (style == QLocale::AlternateQuotation)
1178 res = systemLocale()->query(QSystemLocale::StringToAlternateQuotation,
1179 QVariant::fromValue(str));
1180 if (res.isNull() || style == QLocale::StandardQuotation)
1181 res = systemLocale()->query(QSystemLocale::StringToStandardQuotation,
1182 QVariant::fromValue(str));
1183 if (!res.isNull())
1184 return res.toString();
1185 }
1186#endif
1187
1188 QLocaleData::DataRange start, end;
1189 if (style == QLocale::StandardQuotation) {
1190 start = d->m_data->quoteStart();
1191 end = d->m_data->quoteEnd();
1192 } else {
1193 start = d->m_data->quoteStartAlternate();
1194 end = d->m_data->quoteEndAlternate();
1195 }
1196
1197 return start.viewData(table: single_character_data) % str % end.viewData(table: single_character_data);
1198}

1200/*!
1201 \since 4.8
1202
1203 Returns a string that represents a join of a given \a list of strings with
1204 a separator defined by the locale.
1205*/
1206QString QLocale::createSeparatedList(const QStringList &list) const
1207{
1208 // May be empty if list is empty or sole entry is empty.
1209#ifndef QT_NO_SYSTEMLOCALE
1210 if (d->m_data == &systemLocaleData) {
1211 QVariant res =
1212 systemLocale()->query(QSystemLocale::ListToSeparatedString, QVariant::fromValue(list));
1213
1214 if (!res.isNull())
1215 return res.toString();
1216 }
1217#endif
1218
1219 const qsizetype size = list.size();
1220 if (size < 1)
1221 return QString();
1222
1223 if (size == 1)
1224 return list.at(i: 0);
1225
1226 if (size == 2)
1227 return d->m_data->pairListPattern().getData(
1228 table: list_pattern_part_data).arg(args: list.at(i: 0), args: list.at(i: 1));
1229
1230 QStringView formatStart = d->m_data->startListPattern().viewData(table: list_pattern_part_data);
1231 QStringView formatMid = d->m_data->midListPattern().viewData(table: list_pattern_part_data);
1232 QStringView formatEnd = d->m_data->endListPattern().viewData(table: list_pattern_part_data);
1233 QString result = formatStart.arg(args: list.at(i: 0), args: list.at(i: 1));
1234 for (qsizetype i = 2; i < size - 1; ++i)
1235 result = formatMid.arg(args&: result, args: list.at(i));
1236 result = formatEnd.arg(args&: result, args: list.at(i: size - 1));
1237 return result;
1238}

1320/*!
1321 \brief The short name of this locale.
1322
1323 Returns the language and territory of this locale as a string of the form
1324 "language_territory", where language is a lowercase, two-letter ISO 639
1325 language code, and territory is an uppercase, two- or three-letter ISO 3166
1326 territory code. If the locale has no specified territory, only the language
1327 name is returned.
1328
1329 Even if the QLocale object was constructed with an explicit script, name()
1330 will not contain it for compatibility reasons. Use \l bcp47Name() instead if
1331 you need a full locale name, or construct the string you want to identify a
1332 locale by from those returned by passing its \l language() to \l
1333 languageToCode() and similar for the script and territory.
1334
1335 \sa QLocale(), language(), script(), territory(), bcp47Name(), uiLanguages()
1336*/
1337
1338QString QLocale::name() const
1339{
1340 Language l = language();
1341 if (l == C)
1342 return d->languageCode();
1343
1344 Territory c = territory();
1345 if (c == AnyTerritory)
1346 return d->languageCode();
1347
1348 return d->languageCode() + u'_' + d->territoryCode();
1349}

1351static qlonglong toIntegral_helper(const QLocaleData *d, QStringView str, bool *ok,
1352 QLocale::NumberOptions mode, qlonglong)
1353{
1354 return d->stringToLongLong(str, base: 10, ok, options: mode);
1355}
1356
1357static qulonglong toIntegral_helper(const QLocaleData *d, QStringView str, bool *ok,
1358 QLocale::NumberOptions mode, qulonglong)
1359{
1360 return d->stringToUnsLongLong(str, base: 10, ok, options: mode);
1361}
1362
1363template <typename T> static inline
1364T toIntegral_helper(const QLocalePrivate *d, QStringView str, bool *ok)
1365{
1366 using Int64 =
1367 typename std::conditional<std::is_unsigned<T>::value, qulonglong, qlonglong>::type;
1368
1369 // we select the right overload by the last, unused parameter
1370 Int64 val = toIntegral_helper(d->m_data, str, ok, d->m_numberOptions, Int64());
1371 if (T(val) != val) {
1372 if (ok != nullptr)
1373 *ok = false;
1374 val = 0;
1375 }
1376 return T(val);
1377}

1383 \brief Returns the BCP47 field names joined with dashes.
1384
1385 This combines as many of language, script and territory (and possibly other
1386 BCP47 fields) for this locale as are needed to uniquely specify it. Note
1387 that fields may be omitted if the Unicode consortium's \l {Matching
1388 combinations of language, script and territory}{Likely Subtag Rules} imply
1389 the omitted fields when given those retained. See \l name() for how to

2046/*!
2047 \since 5.14
2048
2049 Returns a localized string representation of the given \a date according
2050 to the specified \a format (see dateFormat()), optionally for a specified
2051 calendar \a cal.
2052
2053 \note Some locales may use formats that limit the range of years they can
2054 represent.
2055*/
2056QString QLocale::toString(QDate date, FormatType format, QCalendar cal) const
2057{
2058 if (!date.isValid())
2059 return QString();
2060
2061#ifndef QT_NO_SYSTEMLOCALE
2062 if (cal.isGregorian() && d->m_data == &systemLocaleData) {
2063 QVariant res = systemLocale()->query(format == LongFormat
2064 ? QSystemLocale::DateToStringLong
2065 : QSystemLocale::DateToStringShort,
2066 date);
2067 if (!res.isNull())
2068 return res.toString();
2069 }
2070#endif
2071
2072 QString format_str = dateFormat(format);
2073 return toString(date, format: format_str, cal);
2074}

2097 return toString(date, format: format_str);

2100static bool timeFormatContainsAP(QStringView format)
2101{
2102 qsizetype i = 0;
2103 while (i < format.size()) {
2104 if (format.at(n: i).unicode() == '\'') {
2105 qt_readEscapedFormatString(format, idx: &i);
2106 continue;
2107 }
2108
2109 if (format.at(n: i).toLower().unicode() == 'a')
2110 return true;
2111
2112 ++i;
2113 }
2114 return false;
2115}

2608/*!
2609 \overload
2610 Returns a string representing the floating-point number \a f.
2611
2612 The form of the representation is controlled by the \a format and \a
2613 precision parameters.
2614
2615 The \a format defaults to \c{'g'}. It can be any of the following:
2616
2617 \table
2618 \header \li Format \li Meaning \li Meaning of \a precision
2619 \row \li \c 'e' \li format as [-]9.9e[+|-]999 \li number of digits \e after the decimal point
2620 \row \li \c 'E' \li format as [-]9.9E[+|-]999 \li "
2621 \row \li \c 'f' \li format as [-]9.9 \li "
2622 \row \li \c 'F' \li same as \c 'f' except for INF and NAN (see below) \li "
2623 \row \li \c 'g' \li use \c 'e' or \c 'f' format, whichever is more concise \li maximum number of significant digits (trailing zeroes are omitted)
2624 \row \li \c 'G' \li use \c 'E' or \c 'F' format, whichever is more concise \li "
2625 \endtable
2626
2627 The special \a precision value QLocale::FloatingPointShortest selects the
2628 shortest representation that, when read as a number, gets back the original floating-point
2629 value. Aside from that, any negative \a precision is ignored in favor of the
2630 default, 6.
2631
2632 For the \c 'e', \c 'f' and \c 'g' formats, positive infinity is represented
2633 as "inf", negative infinity as "-inf" and floating-point NaN (not-a-number)
2634 values are represented as "nan". For the \c 'E', \c 'F' and \c 'G' formats,
2635 "INF" and "NAN" are used instead. This does not vary with locale.
2636
2637 \sa toDouble(), numberOptions(), exponential(), decimalPoint(), zeroDigit(),
2638 positiveSign(), percent(), toCurrencyString(), formattedDataSize(),
2639 QLocale::FloatingPointPrecisionOption
2640*/
2641
2642QString QLocale::toString(double f, char format, int precision) const
2643{
2644 QLocaleData::DoubleForm form = QLocaleData::DFDecimal;
2645 uint flags = isAsciiUpper(c: format) ? QLocaleData::CapitalEorX : 0;
2646
2647 switch (QtMiscUtils::toAsciiLower(ch: format)) {
2648 case 'f':
2649 form = QLocaleData::DFDecimal;
2650 break;
2651 case 'e':
2652 form = QLocaleData::DFExponent;
2653 break;
2654 case 'g':
2655 form = QLocaleData::DFSignificantDigits;
2656 break;
2657 default:
2658 break;
2659 }
2660
2661 if (!(d->m_numberOptions & OmitGroupSeparator))
2662 flags |= QLocaleData::GroupDigits;
2663 if (!(d->m_numberOptions & OmitLeadingZeroInExponent))
2664 flags |= QLocaleData::ZeroPadExponent;
2665 if (d->m_numberOptions & IncludeTrailingZeroesAfterDot)
2666 flags |= QLocaleData::AddTrailingZeroes;
2667 return d->m_data->doubleToString(d: f, precision, form, width: -1, flags);
2668}

2670/*!

2672
2673 Returns a QLocale object initialized to the "C" locale.
2674
2675 This locale is based on en_US but with various quirks of its own, such as
2676 simplified number formatting and its own date formatting. It implements the

2680 Among other things, this means its collation order is based on the ASCII
2681 values of letters, so that (for case-sensitive sorting) all upper-case

2711/*!
2712 Returns a list of valid locale objects that match the given \a language, \a
2713 script and \a territory.
2714
2715 Getting a list of all locales:
2716 QList<QLocale> allLocales = QLocale::matchingLocales(QLocale::AnyLanguage, QLocale::AnyScript,
2717 QLocale::AnyTerritory);
2718
2719 Getting a list of locales suitable for Russia:
2720 QList<QLocale> locales = QLocale::matchingLocales(QLocale::AnyLanguage, QLocale::AnyScript,
2721 QLocale::Russia);
2722*/
2723QList<QLocale> QLocale::matchingLocales(QLocale::Language language, QLocale::Script script,
2724 QLocale::Territory territory)
2725{
2726 const QLocaleId filter { .language_id: language, .script_id: script, .territory_id: territory };
2727 if (!filter.isValid())
2728 return QList<QLocale>();
2729
2730 if (language == QLocale::C)
2731 return QList<QLocale>() << QLocale(QLocale::C);
2732
2733 QList<QLocale> result;
2734 if (filter.matchesAll())
2735 result.reserve(size: locale_data_size);
2736
2737 quint16 index = locale_index[language];
2738 // There may be no matches, for some languages (e.g. Abkhazian at CLDR v39).
2739 while (filter.acceptLanguage(lang: locale_data[index].m_language_id)) {
2740 const QLocaleId id = locale_data[index].id();
2741 if (filter.acceptScriptTerritory(other: id)) {
2742 result.append(t: QLocale(*(id.language_id == C ? c_private()
2743 : new QLocalePrivate(locale_data + index, index))));
2744 }
2745 ++index;
2746 }
2747
2748 return result;
2749}

2846
2847static QString rawMonthName(const QCalendarLocale &localeData,
2848 const char16_t *monthsData, int month,
2849 QLocale::FormatType type)
2850{
2851 QLocaleData::DataRange range;

2853 case QLocale::LongFormat:
2854 range = localeData.longMonth();
2855 break;
2856 case QLocale::ShortFormat:

3545QString QLocaleData::doubleToString(double d, int precision, DoubleForm form,
3546 int width, unsigned flags) const
3547{

3549 // DFSignificantDigits, the double-conversion library does treat it
3550 // specially for the other forms, shedding trailing zeros for DFDecimal and
3551 // using the shortest mantissa that faithfully represents the value for
3552 // DFExponent.
3553 if (precision != QLocale::FloatingPointShortest && precision < 0)
3554 precision = 6;
3555 if (width < 0)
3556 width = 0;
3557

3560 if (precision == QLocale::FloatingPointShortest)
3561 bufSize += std::numeric_limits<double>::max_digits10;
3562 else if (form == DFDecimal && qIsFinite(d))
3563 bufSize += wholePartSpace(d: qAbs(t: d)) + precision;
3564 else // Add extra digit due to different interpretations of precision.
3565 bufSize += qMax(a: 2, b: precision) + 1; // Must also be big enough for "nan" or "inf"
3566
3567 QVarLengthArray<char> buf(bufSize);
3568 int length;
3569 bool negative = false;
3570 qt_doubleToAscii(d, form, precision, buf: buf.data(), bufSize, sign&: negative, length, decpt);
3571
3572 const QString prefix = signPrefix(negative: negative && !isZero(d), flags);
3573 QString numStr;
3574
3575 if (length == 3
3576 && (qstrncmp(str1: buf.data(), str2: "inf", len: 3) == 0 || qstrncmp(str1: buf.data(), str2: "nan", len: 3) == 0)) {
3577 numStr = QString::fromLatin1(str: buf.data(), size: length);
3578 } else { // Handle finite values
3579 const QString zero = zeroDigit();
3580 QString digits = QString::fromLatin1(str: buf.data(), size: length);
3581
3582 if (zero == u"0") {
3583 // No need to convert digits.
3584 Q_ASSERT(std::all_of(buf.cbegin(), buf.cbegin() + length, [](char ch)
3585 { return '0' <= ch && ch <= '9'; }));
3586 // That check is taken care of in unicodeForDigits, below.
3587 } else if (zero.size() == 2 && zero.at(i: 0).isHighSurrogate()) {
3588 const char32_t zeroUcs4 = QChar::surrogateToUcs4(high: zero.at(i: 0), low: zero.at(i: 1));
3589 QString converted;
3590 converted.reserve(asize: 2 * digits.size());
3591 for (QChar ch : std::as_const(t&: digits)) {
3592 const char32_t digit = unicodeForDigit(digit: ch.unicode() - '0', zero: zeroUcs4);
3593 Q_ASSERT(QChar::requiresSurrogates(digit));
3594 converted.append(c: QChar::highSurrogate(ucs4: digit));
3595 converted.append(c: QChar::lowSurrogate(ucs4: digit));
3596 }
3597 digits = converted;
3598 } else {
3599 Q_ASSERT(zero.size() == 1);
3600 Q_ASSERT(!zero.at(0).isSurrogate());
3601 char16_t z = zero.at(i: 0).unicode();
3602 char16_t *const value = reinterpret_cast<char16_t *>(digits.data());
3603 for (qsizetype i = 0; i < digits.size(); ++i)
3604 value[i] = unicodeForDigit(digit: value[i] - '0', zero: z);
3605 }
3606
3607 const bool mustMarkDecimal = flags & ForcePoint;
3608 const bool groupDigits = flags & GroupDigits;
3609 const int minExponentDigits = flags & ZeroPadExponent ? 2 : 1;
3610 switch (form) {
3611 case DFExponent:
3612 numStr = exponentForm(digits: std::move(digits), decpt, precision, pm: PMDecimalDigits,
3613 mustMarkDecimal, minExponentDigits);
3614 break;
3615 case DFDecimal:
3616 numStr = decimalForm(digits: std::move(digits), decpt, precision, pm: PMDecimalDigits,
3617 mustMarkDecimal, groupDigits);
3618 break;
3619 case DFSignificantDigits: {
3620 PrecisionMode mode = (flags & AddTrailingZeroes) ?
3621 PMSignificantDigits : PMChopTrailingZeros;
3622
3623 /* POSIX specifies sprintf() to follow fprintf(), whose 'g/G'
3624 format says; with P = 6 if precision unspecified else 1 if
3625 precision is 0 else precision; when 'e/E' would have exponent
3626 X, use:
3627 * 'f/F' if P > X >= -4, with precision P-1-X
3628 * 'e/E' otherwise, with precision P-1
3629 Helpfully, we already have mapped precision < 0 to 6 - except
3630 for F.P.Shortest mode, which is its own story - and those of
3631 our callers with unspecified precision either used 6 or -1
3632 for it.
3633 */
3634 bool useDecimal;
3635 if (precision == QLocale::FloatingPointShortest) {
3636 // Find out which representation is shorter.
3637 // Set bias to everything added to exponent form but not
3638 // decimal, minus the converse.
3639
3640 // Exponent adds separator, sign and digits:
3641 int bias = 2 + minExponentDigits;
3642 // Decimal form may get grouping separators inserted:
3643 if (groupDigits && decpt >= m_grouping_top + m_grouping_least)
3644 bias -= (decpt - m_grouping_top - m_grouping_least) / m_grouping_higher + 1;
3645 // X = decpt - 1 needs two digits if decpt > 10:
3646 if (decpt > 10 && minExponentDigits == 1)
3647 ++bias;
3648 // Assume digitCount < 95, so we can ignore the 3-digit
3649 // exponent case (we'll set useDecimal false anyway).
3650
3651 const qsizetype digitCount = digits.size() / zero.size();
3652 if (!mustMarkDecimal) {
3653 // Decimal separator is skipped if at end; adjust if
3654 // that happens for only one form:
3655 if (digitCount <= decpt && digitCount > 1)
3656 ++bias; // decimal but not exponent
3657 else if (digitCount == 1 && decpt <= 0)
3658 --bias; // exponent but not decimal
3659 }
3660 // When 0 < decpt <= digitCount, the forms have equal digit
3661 // counts, plus things bias has taken into account;
3662 // otherwise decimal form's digit count is right-padded with
3663 // zeros to decpt, when decpt is positive, otherwise it's
3664 // left-padded with 1 - decpt zeros.
3665 useDecimal = (decpt <= 0 ? 1 - decpt <= bias
3666 : decpt <= digitCount ? 0 <= bias
3667 : decpt <= digitCount + bias);
3668 } else {
3669 // X == decpt - 1, POSIX's P; -4 <= X < P iff -4 < decpt <= P
3670 Q_ASSERT(precision >= 0);
3671 useDecimal = decpt > -4 && decpt <= (precision ? precision : 1);
3672 }
3673
3674 numStr = useDecimal
3675 ? decimalForm(digits: std::move(digits), decpt, precision, pm: mode,
3676 mustMarkDecimal, groupDigits)
3677 : exponentForm(digits: std::move(digits), decpt, precision, pm: mode,
3678 mustMarkDecimal, minExponentDigits);
3679 break;
3680 }
3681 }
3682
3683 // Pad with zeros. LeftAdjusted overrides ZeroPadded.
3684 if (flags & ZeroPadded && !(flags & LeftAdjusted)) {
3685 for (qsizetype i = numStr.size() / zero.size() + prefix.size(); i < width; ++i)
3686 numStr.prepend(s: zero);
3687 }
3688 }
3689
3690 return prefix + (flags & CapitalEorX ? std::move(numStr).toUpper() : numStr);
3691}
3692
3693QString QLocaleData::decimalForm(QString &&digits, int decpt, int precision,
3694 PrecisionMode pm, bool mustMarkDecimal,
3695 bool groupDigits) const
3696{
3697 const QString zero = zeroDigit();
3698 const auto digitWidth = zero.size();
3699 Q_ASSERT(digitWidth == 1 || digitWidth == 2);
3700 Q_ASSERT(digits.size() % digitWidth == 0);
3701
3702 // Separator needs to go at index decpt: so add zeros before or after the
3703 // given digits, if they don't reach that position already:
3704 if (decpt < 0) {
3705 for (; decpt < 0; ++decpt)
3706 digits.prepend(s: zero);
3707 } else {
3708 for (qsizetype i = digits.size() / digitWidth; i < decpt; ++i)
3709 digits.append(s: zero);
3710 }
3711
3712 switch (pm) {
3713 case PMDecimalDigits:
3714 for (qsizetype i = digits.size() / digitWidth - decpt; i < precision; ++i)
3715 digits.append(s: zero);
3716 break;
3717 case PMSignificantDigits:
3718 for (qsizetype i = digits.size() / digitWidth; i < precision; ++i)
3719 digits.append(s: zero);
3720 break;
3721 case PMChopTrailingZeros:
3722 Q_ASSERT(digits.size() / digitWidth <= qMax(decpt, 1) || !digits.endsWith(zero));
3723 break;
3724 }
3725
3726 if (mustMarkDecimal || decpt < digits.size() / digitWidth)
3727 digits.insert(i: decpt * digitWidth, s: decimalPoint());
3728
3729 if (groupDigits) {
3730 const QString group = groupSeparator();
3731 qsizetype i = decpt - m_grouping_least;
3732 if (i >= m_grouping_top) {
3733 digits.insert(i: i * digitWidth, s: group);
3734 while ((i -= m_grouping_higher) >= m_grouping_top)
3735 digits.insert(i: i * digitWidth, s: group);
3736 }
3737 }
3738
3739 if (decpt == 0)
3740 digits.prepend(s: zero);
3741
3742 return std::move(digits);
3743}
3744
3745QString QLocaleData::exponentForm(QString &&digits, int decpt, int precision,
3746 PrecisionMode pm, bool mustMarkDecimal,
3747 int minExponentDigits) const
3748{
3749 const QString zero = zeroDigit();
3750 const auto digitWidth = zero.size();
3751 Q_ASSERT(digitWidth == 1 || digitWidth == 2);
3752 Q_ASSERT(digits.size() % digitWidth == 0);
3753
3754 switch (pm) {
3755 case PMDecimalDigits:
3756 for (qsizetype i = digits.size() / digitWidth; i < precision + 1; ++i)
3757 digits.append(s: zero);
3758 break;
3759 case PMSignificantDigits:
3760 for (qsizetype i = digits.size() / digitWidth; i < precision; ++i)
3761 digits.append(s: zero);
3762 break;
3763 case PMChopTrailingZeros:
3764 Q_ASSERT(digits.size() / digitWidth <= 1 || !digits.endsWith(zero));
3765 break;
3766 }
3767
3768 if (mustMarkDecimal || digits.size() > digitWidth)
3769 digits.insert(i: digitWidth, s: decimalPoint());
3770
3771 digits.append(s: exponentSeparator());
3772 digits.append(s: longLongToString(l: decpt - 1, precision: minExponentDigits, base: 10, width: -1, flags: AlwaysShowSign));
3773
3774 return std::move(digits);
3775}

3811
3812QString QLocaleData::applyIntegerFormatting(QString &&numStr, bool negative, int precision,
3813 int base, int width, unsigned flags) const
3814{
3815 const QString zero = base == 10 ? zeroDigit() : QStringLiteral("0");
3816 const auto digitWidth = zero.size();
3817 const auto digitCount = numStr.size() / digitWidth;
3818
3819 const auto basePrefix = [&] () -> QStringView {
3820 if (flags & ShowBase) {
3821 const bool upper = flags & UppercaseBase;
3822 if (base == 16)
3823 return upper ? u"0X" : u"0x";
3824 if (base == 2)
3825 return upper ? u"0B" : u"0b";
3826 if (base == 8 && !numStr.startsWith(s: zero))
3827 return zero;
3828 }
3829 return {};
3830 }();
3831
3832 const QString prefix = signPrefix(negative, flags) + basePrefix;
3833 // Count how much of width we've used up. Each digit counts as one
3834 qsizetype usedWidth = digitCount + prefix.size();
3835
3836 if (base == 10 && flags & GroupDigits) {
3837 const QString group = groupSeparator();
3838 qsizetype i = digitCount - m_grouping_least;
3839 if (i >= m_grouping_top) {
3840 numStr.insert(i: i * digitWidth, s: group);
3841 ++usedWidth;
3842 while ((i -= m_grouping_higher) >= m_grouping_top) {
3843 numStr.insert(i: i * digitWidth, s: group);
3844 ++usedWidth;
3845 }
3846 }
3847 // TODO: should we group any zero-padding we add later ?
3848 }
3849
3850 const bool noPrecision = precision == -1;
3851 if (noPrecision)
3852 precision = 1;
3853
3854 for (qsizetype i = numStr.size(); i < precision; ++i) {
3855 numStr.prepend(s: zero);
3856 usedWidth++;
3857 }
3858
3859 // LeftAdjusted overrides ZeroPadded; and sprintf() only pads when
3860 // precision is not specified in the format string.
3861 if (noPrecision && flags & ZeroPadded && !(flags & LeftAdjusted)) {
3862 for (qsizetype i = usedWidth; i < width; ++i)
3863 numStr.prepend(s: zero);
3864 }
3865
3866 QString result(flags & CapitalEorX ? std::move(numStr).toUpper() : std::move(numStr));
3867 if (prefix.size())
3868 result.prepend(s: prefix);
3869 return result;
3870}

3872/*
3873 Converts a number in locale to its representation in the C locale.
3874 Only has to guarantee that a string that is a correct representation of
3875 a number will be converted.
3876
3877 Note: only QString integer-parsing methods have a base parameter (hence need
3878 to cope with letters as possible digits); but these are now all routed via
3879 byteArrayToU?LongLong(), so no longer come via here. The QLocale
3880 number-parsers only work in decimal, so don't have to cope with any digits
3881 other than 0 through 9.
3882*/
3883bool QLocaleData::numberToCLocale(QStringView s, QLocale::NumberOptions number_options,
3884 CharBuff *result) const
3885{
3886 s = s.trimmed();
3887 if (s.size() < 1)
3888 return false;
3889
3890 const QChar *uc = s.data();
3891 auto length = s.size();
3892 decltype(length) idx = 0;
3893
3894 // Digit-grouping details (all modes):
3895 qsizetype digitsInGroup = 0;
3896 qsizetype last_separator_idx = -1;
3897 qsizetype start_of_digits_idx = -1;
3898
3899 // Floating-point details (non-integer modes):
3900 qsizetype decpt_idx = -1;
3901 qsizetype exponent_idx = -1;
3902
3903 char last = '\0';
3904 while (idx < length) {
3905 const QStringView in = QStringView(uc + idx, uc[idx].isHighSurrogate() ? 2 : 1);
3906
3907 char out = numericToCLocale(in);
3908 if (out == 0) {
3909 // Allow ASCII letters of inf, nan:
3910 if (in.size() != 1)
3911 return false;
3912 char16_t ch = in.front().unicode();
3913 if (ch > 'n')
3914 return false;
3915 out = int(ch | 0x20); // tolower(), when ch is a letter
3916 if (out != 'a' && out != 'f' && out != 'i' && out != 'n')
3917 return false;
3918 } else if (out == '.') {
3919 // Fail if more than one decimal point or point after e
3920 if (decpt_idx != -1 || exponent_idx != -1)
3921 return false;
3922 decpt_idx = idx;
3923 } else if (out == 'e') {
3924 exponent_idx = idx;
3925 }
3926
3927 if (number_options.testFlag(flag: QLocale::RejectLeadingZeroInExponent)) {
3928 if (exponent_idx != -1 && out == '0' && idx < length - 1) {
3929 // After the exponent there can only be '+', '-' or digits.
3930 // If we find a '0' directly after some non-digit, then that is a leading zero.
3931 if (last < '0' || last > '9')
3932 return false;
3933 }
3934 }
3935
3936 if (number_options.testFlag(flag: QLocale::RejectTrailingZeroesAfterDot)) {
3937 // If we've seen a decimal point and the last character after the exponent is 0, then
3938 // that is a trailing zero.
3939 if (decpt_idx >= 0 && idx == exponent_idx && last == '0')
3940 return false;
3941 }
3942
3943 if (!number_options.testFlag(flag: QLocale::RejectGroupSeparator)) {
3944 if (out >= '0' && out <= '9') {
3945 if (start_of_digits_idx == -1)
3946 start_of_digits_idx = idx;
3947 ++digitsInGroup;
3948 } else if (out == ',') {
3949 // Don't allow group chars after the decimal point or exponent
3950 if (decpt_idx != -1 || exponent_idx != -1)
3951 return false;
3952
3953 if (last_separator_idx == -1) {
3954 // Check distance from the beginning of the digits:
3955 if (start_of_digits_idx == -1 || m_grouping_top > digitsInGroup
3956 || digitsInGroup >= m_grouping_higher + m_grouping_top) {
3957 return false;
3958 }
3959 } else {
3960 // Check distance from the last separator:
3961 if (digitsInGroup != m_grouping_higher)
3962 return false;
3963 }
3964
3965 last_separator_idx = idx;
3966 digitsInGroup = 0;
3967 } else if (out == '.' || idx == exponent_idx) {
3968 // Were there enough digits since the last separator?
3969 if (last_separator_idx != -1 && digitsInGroup != m_grouping_least)
3970 return false;
3971 // If we saw no separator, should we fail if
3972 // digitsInGroup > m_grouping_top + m_grouping_least ?
3973
3974 // stop processing separators
3975 last_separator_idx = -1;
3976 }
3977 } else if (out == ',') {
3978 return false;
3979 }
3980
3981 last = out;
3982 if (out != ',') // Leave group separators out of the result.
3983 result->append(t: out);
3984 idx += in.size();
3985 }
3986
3987 if (!number_options.testFlag(flag: QLocale::RejectGroupSeparator)) {
3988 // group separator post-processing
3989 // did we end in a separator?
3990 if (last_separator_idx + 1 == idx)
3991 return false;
3992 // Were there enough digits since the last separator?
3993 if (last_separator_idx != -1 && digitsInGroup != m_grouping_least)
3994 return false;
3995 // If we saw no separator, and no decimal point, should we fail if
3996 // digitsInGroup > m_grouping_top + m_grouping_least ?
3997 }
3998
3999 if (number_options.testFlag(flag: QLocale::RejectTrailingZeroesAfterDot)) {
4000 // In decimal form, the last character can be a trailing zero if we've seen a decpt.
4001 if (decpt_idx != -1 && exponent_idx == -1 && last == '0')
4002 return false;
4003 }
4004
4005 result->append(t: '\0');
4006 return idx == length;
4007}
4008
4009bool QLocaleData::validateChars(QStringView str, NumberMode numMode, QByteArray *buff,
4010 int decDigits, QLocale::NumberOptions number_options) const
4011{
4012 buff->clear();
4013 buff->reserve(asize: str.size());
4014
4015 enum { Whole, Fractional, Exponent } state = Whole;
4016 const bool scientific = numMode == DoubleScientificMode;
4017 char last = '\0';
4018
4019 for (qsizetype i = 0; i < str.size();) {
4020 const QStringView in = str.mid(pos: i, n: str.at(n: i).isHighSurrogate() ? 2 : 1);
4021 char c = numericToCLocale(in);
4022
4023 if (isAsciiDigit(c)) {
4024 switch (state) {
4025 case Whole:
4026 // Nothing special to do (unless we want to check grouping sizes).
4027 break;
4028 case Fractional:
4029 // If a double has too many digits in its fractional part it is Invalid.
4030 if (decDigits-- == 0)
4031 return false;
4032 break;
4033 case Exponent:
4034 if (last < '0' || last > '9') {
4035 // This is the first digit in the exponent (there may have beena '+'
4036 // or '-' in before). If it's a zero, the exponent is zero-padded.
4037 if (c == '0' && (number_options & QLocale::RejectLeadingZeroInExponent))
4038 return false;
4039 }
4040 break;
4041 }
4042
4043 } else {
4044 switch (c) {
4045 case '.':
4046 // If an integer has a decimal point, it is Invalid.
4047 // A double can only have one, at the end of its whole-number part.
4048 if (numMode == IntegerMode || state != Whole)
4049 return false;
4050 // Even when decDigits is 0, we do allow the decimal point to be
4051 // present - just as long as no digits follow it.
4052
4053 state = Fractional;
4054 break;
4055
4056 case '+':
4057 case '-':
4058 // A sign can only appear at the start or after the e of scientific:
4059 if (last != '\0' && !(scientific && last == 'e'))
4060 return false;
4061 break;
4062
4063 case ',':
4064 // Grouping is only allowed after a digit in the whole-number portion:
4065 if ((number_options & QLocale::RejectGroupSeparator) || state != Whole
4066 || last < '0' || last > '9') {
4067 return false;
4068 }
4069 // We could check grouping sizes are correct, but fixup()s are
4070 // probably better off correcting any misplacement instead.
4071 break;
4072
4073 case 'e':
4074 // Only one e is allowed and only in scientific:
4075 if (!scientific || state == Exponent)
4076 return false;
4077 state = Exponent;
4078 break;
4079
4080 default:
4081 // Nothing else can validly appear in a number.
4082 // In fact, numericToCLocale() must have returned 0. If anyone changes
4083 // it to return something else, we probably need to handle it here !
4084 Q_ASSERT(!c);
4085 return false;
4086 }
4087 }
4088
4089 last = c;
4090 if (c != ',') // Skip grouping
4091 buff->append(c);
4092 i += in.size();
4093 }
4094
4095 return true;
4096}

4140{

4143 if (used <= 0) {
4144 if (ok != nullptr)
4145 *ok = false;
4146 return 0;
4147 }
4148
4149 if (used < len && num[used] != '\0') {
4150 while (used < len && ascii_isspace(c: num[used]))
4151 ++used;

4155 // we stopped at a non-digit character after converting some digits

4192/*!
4193 \since 4.8
4194
4195 \enum QLocale::CurrencySymbolFormat
4196
4197 Specifies the format of the currency symbol.
4198
4199 \value CurrencyIsoCode a ISO-4217 code of the currency.
4200 \value CurrencySymbol a currency symbol.

4209{

4212 auto res = systemLocale()->query(QSystemLocale::CurrencySymbol, format).toString();
4213 if (!res.isEmpty())
4214 return res;
4215 }
4216#endif
4217 switch (format) {
4218 case CurrencySymbol:
4219 return d->m_data->currencySymbol().getData(table: currency_symbol_data);
4220 case CurrencyDisplayName:
4221 return d->m_data->currencyDisplayName().getData(table: currency_display_name_data);
4222 case CurrencyIsoCode: {
4223 const char *code = d->m_data->m_currency_iso_code;
4224 if (auto len = qstrnlen(str: code, maxlen: 3))
4225 return QString::fromLatin1(str: code, size: qsizetype(len));
4226 break;
4227 }
4228 }
4229 return QString();
4230}

4323/*!
4324 \since 5.10
4325
4326 \enum QLocale::DataSizeFormat
4327
4328 Specifies the format for representation of data quantities.
4329
4330 \omitvalue DataSizeBase1000
4331 \omitvalue DataSizeSIQuantifiers
4332 \value DataSizeIecFormat format using base 1024 and IEC prefixes: KiB, MiB, GiB, ...
4333 \value DataSizeTraditionalFormat format using base 1024 and SI prefixes: kB, MB, GB, ...
4334 \value DataSizeSIFormat format using base 1000 and SI prefixes: kB, MB, GB, ...
4335
4336 \sa formattedDataSize()
4337*/
4338
4339/*!
4340 \since 5.10
4341
4342 Converts a size in bytes to a human-readable localized string, comprising a
4343 number and a quantified unit. The quantifier is chosen such that the number
4344 is at least one, and as small as possible. For example if \a bytes is
4345 16384, \a precision is 2, and \a format is \l DataSizeIecFormat (the
4346 default), this function returns "16.00 KiB"; for 1330409069609 bytes it
4347 returns "1.21 GiB"; and so on. If \a format is \l DataSizeIecFormat or
4348 \l DataSizeTraditionalFormat, the given number of bytes is divided by a
4349 power of 1024, with result less than 1024; for \l DataSizeSIFormat, it is
4350 divided by a power of 1000, with result less than 1000.
4351 \c DataSizeIecFormat uses the new IEC standard quantifiers Ki, Mi and so on,
4352 whereas \c DataSizeSIFormat uses the older SI quantifiers k, M, etc., and
4353 \c DataSizeTraditionalFormat abuses them.
4354*/
4355QString QLocale::formattedDataSize(qint64 bytes, int precision, DataSizeFormats format) const
4356{
4357 int power, base = 1000;
4358 if (!bytes) {
4359 power = 0;
4360 } else if (format & DataSizeBase1000) {
4361 power = int(std::log10(x: qAbs(t: bytes)) / 3);
4362 } else { // Compute log2(bytes) / 10:
4363 power = int((63 - qCountLeadingZeroBits(v: quint64(qAbs(t: bytes)))) / 10);
4364 base = 1024;
4365 }
4366 // Only go to doubles if we'll be using a quantifier:
4367 const QString number = power
4368 ? toString(f: bytes / std::pow(x: double(base), y: power), format: 'f', precision: qMin(a: precision, b: 3 * power))
4369 : toString(i: bytes);
4370
4371 // We don't support sizes in units larger than exbibytes because
4372 // the number of bytes would not fit into qint64.
4373 Q_ASSERT(power <= 6 && power >= 0);
4374 QStringView unit;
4375 if (power > 0) {
4376 QLocaleData::DataRange range = (format & DataSizeSIQuantifiers)
4377 ? d->m_data->byteAmountSI() : d->m_data->byteAmountIEC();
4378 unit = range.viewListEntry(table: byte_unit_data, index: power - 1);
4379 } else {
4380 unit = d->m_data->byteCount().viewData(table: byte_unit_data);
4381 }
4382
4383 return number + u' ' + unit;
4384}

4386/*!
4387 \since 4.8
4388 \brief List of locale names for use in selecting translations
4389
4390 Each entry in the returned list is the dash-joined name of a locale,
4391 suitable to the user's preferences for what to translate the UI into. For
4392 example, if the user has configured their system to use English as used in
4393 the USA, the list would be "en-Latn-US", "en-US", "en". The order of entries
4394 is the order in which to check for translations; earlier items in the list
4395 are to be preferred over later ones.
4396
4397 Most likely you do not need to use this function directly, but just pass the
4398 QLocale object to the QTranslator::load() function.
4399
4400 \sa QTranslator, bcp47Name()
4401*/
4402QStringList QLocale::uiLanguages() const
4403{
4404 QStringList uiLanguages;
4405 QList<QLocaleId> localeIds;
4406#ifdef QT_NO_SYSTEMLOCALE
4407 constexpr bool isSystem = false;
4408#else
4409 const bool isSystem = d->m_data == &systemLocaleData;
4410 if (isSystem) {
4411 uiLanguages = systemLocale()->query(QSystemLocale::UILanguages).toStringList();
4412 // ... but we need to include likely-adjusted forms of each of those, too.
4413 // For now, collect up locale Ids representing the entries, for later processing:
4414 for (const auto &entry : std::as_const(uiLanguages))
4415 localeIds.append(QLocaleId::fromName(entry));
4416 if (localeIds.isEmpty())
4417 localeIds.append(systemLocale()->fallbackLocale().d->m_data->id());
4418 // If the system locale (isn't C and) didn't include itself in the list,
4419 // or as fallback, presume to know better than it and put its name
4420 // first. (Known issue, QTBUG-104930, on some macOS versions when in
4421 // locale en_DE.) Our translation system might have a translation for a
4422 // locale the platform doesn't believe in.
4423 const QString name = bcp47Name();
4424 if (!name.isEmpty() && language() != C && !uiLanguages.contains(name)) {
4425 // That uses contains(name) as a cheap pre-test, but there may be an
4426 // entry that matches this on purging likely subtags.
4427 const QLocaleId mine = d->m_data->id().withLikelySubtagsRemoved();
4428 const auto isMine = [mine](const QString &entry) {
4429 return QLocaleId::fromName(entry).withLikelySubtagsRemoved() == mine;
4430 };
4431 if (std::none_of(uiLanguages.constBegin(), uiLanguages.constEnd(), isMine)) {
4432 localeIds.prepend(d->m_data->id());
4433 uiLanguages.prepend(name);
4434 }
4435 }
4436 } else
4437#endif
4438 {
4439 localeIds.append(t: d->m_data->id());
4440 }
4441 for (qsizetype i = localeIds.size(); i-- > 0; ) {
4442 QLocaleId id = localeIds.at(i);
4443 qsizetype j;
4444 QByteArray prior;
4445 if (isSystem && i < uiLanguages.size()) {
4446 // Adding likely-adjusted forms to system locale's list.
4447 // Name the locale is derived from:
4448 prior = uiLanguages.at(i).toLatin1();
4449 // Insert just after the entry we're supplementing:
4450 j = i + 1;
4451 } else if (id.language_id == C) {
4452 // Attempt no likely sub-tag amendments to C:
4453 uiLanguages.append(t: QString::fromLatin1(ba: id.name()));
4454 continue;
4455 } else {
4456 // Plain locale or empty system uiLanguages; just append.
4457 prior = id.name();
4458 uiLanguages.append(t: QString::fromLatin1(ba: prior));
4459 j = uiLanguages.size();
4460 }
4461
4462 const QLocaleId max = id.withLikelySubtagsAdded();
4463 const QLocaleId min = max.withLikelySubtagsRemoved();
4464
4465 // Include minimal version (last) unless it's what our locale is derived from:
4466 if (auto name = min.name(); name != prior)
4467 uiLanguages.insert(i: j, t: QString::fromLatin1(ba: name));
4468 else if (!isSystem)
4469 --j; // bcp47Name() matches min(): put more specific forms *before* it.
4470
4471 if (id.script_id) {
4472 // Include scriptless version if likely-equivalent and distinct:
4473 id.script_id = 0;
4474 if (id != min && id.withLikelySubtagsAdded() == max) {
4475 if (auto name = id.name(); name != prior)
4476 uiLanguages.insert(i: j, t: QString::fromLatin1(ba: name));
4477 }
4478 }
4479
4480 if (!id.territory_id) {
4481 Q_ASSERT(!min.territory_id);
4482 Q_ASSERT(!id.script_id); // because we just cleared it.
4483 // Include version with territory if it likely-equivalent and distinct:
4484 id.territory_id = max.territory_id;
4485 if (id != max && id.withLikelySubtagsAdded() == max) {
4486 if (auto name = id.name(); name != prior)
4487 uiLanguages.insert(i: j, t: QString::fromLatin1(ba: name));
4488 }
4489 }
4490
4491 // Include version with all likely sub-tags (first) if distinct from the rest:
4492 if (max != min && max != id) {
4493 if (auto name = max.name(); name != prior)
4494 uiLanguages.insert(i: j, t: QString::fromLatin1(ba: name));
4495 }
4496 }
4497 return uiLanguages;
4498}
